{{other uses of|Jnet}} [[Image:Jnet.png|thumb|300px|Jewish Learning Network logo.]] The '''Jewish Learning Network''' or '''JNET''' is an [[adult education]] program run by the [[Chabad-Lubavitch]] movement. It is a division of the Chabad movement's educational arm, [[Merkos L'Inyonei Chinuch]].<ref name="LubavitchListing">[http://lubavitch.com/centers/detail.html?id=3201 Lubavitch.com. "Jnet - Jewish Learning Network". ''Lubavitch.com''.]</ref><ref name="Chabad.orgArticle">[http://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/2372138/jewish/Making-the-Most-of-Torah-by-Telephone.htm Posner, Menachem. "Making the Most of Torah by Telephone". ''Chabad.org''. October 27, 2013.]</ref><ref name="JnetAbout">[http://www.jnet.org/templates/jnet/article_cdo/aid/1283360/jewish/About-Us.htm Jnet.com. "About Us". ''Jnet.com: Jewish Learning Network'']</ref><ref name="CrownHeightsArticle">[http://crownheights.info/psa/398870/jnet-announces-chai-elul-learning-campaign/ "Jnet Announces Chai Elul Learning Campaign". ''Crownheights.info''. August 22, 2013.]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Worldwide Release of Medicine and Morals|url=https://www.jlicentral.com/news.php?task=fullstory&NID=223|publisher=www.jlicentral.com|accessdate=Sep 24, 2014}}</ref>
==Founding== "JNet" is a non-profit organization acting under [[Merkos L'Inyonei Chinuch]], the central educational organization of the [[Chabad-Lubavitch]] movement.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jewish institute: Course on medicine and morals|url=https://www.jlicentral.com/news.php?task=fullstory&NID=227|publisher=Jlicentral.com|accessdate=Sep 24, 2014}}</ref> JNet was founded in November, 2005 as an adult education resource. The program matches registrants with volunteers based on the registrant's study request. Registrants often have little Jewish education, while volunteers are often Chabad-raised and schooled.<ref name="JnetAbout" /><ref name="Chabad.orgArticle" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Jewish Learning Institute: Medicine & Morals|url=http://www.jewishidaho.com/templates/articlecco_cdo/aid/1283416/jewish/Medicine-Morals.htm|publisher=jewishidaho.com|accessdate=Sep 24, 2014}}</ref>
